The paper deals with a problem related to the Coupon Collector problem, which is a well-known topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and theoretical computer science (cs.CC). The problem involves generating words of a certain length with a given probability distribution, which can be seen as a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also presents a general theorem that can be applied to a wide range of languages, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.SI).
